      | Studio Manager

    p
      | We are looking for a studio manager to ensure the smooth running of our studio as well as help to improve company procedures and day-to-day operations. If you are highly organised, enthusiastic and hardworking with the ability to multitask and prioritise under pressure this might be the job for you. You will play a huge part in ensuring the smooth day-to-day running of our studio

    h2.character
      | Is this you ?
    ul.list
      li
        | You thrive in a faced-paced environment
      li
        | You have strong organisational and time-management skills
      li
        | You love to communicate and are obsessive about the details and do all this with a big smile on your face
      li
        | You have proven experience as an office manager, front office manager or administrative assistant or knowledge of office administrator responsibilities, systems, and procedures
      li
        | You have a creative mind with an ability to suggest improvements
      li
        | You have excellent communication skills as well as the ability to easily connect with people
      li
        | You are an energetic professional who doesn't mind wearing multiple hats
      li
        | You are well organized, flexible and enjoy the administrative challenges of supporting an office of diverse people.
      li
        | You have a bachelor degree or equivalent and two years of experience in office administration
      li
        | You have excellent computer skills, including a high degree of proficiency in Microsoft Word, Excel, Outlook, and PowerPoint.

