      | Role:

    ul.list
      li
        | Oversee general office operations as well as supervise, mentor, train, and coach our office staff and delegate work to ensure maximum productivity.
      li
        | Ensuring all projects are planned and resourced for in the most effective way possible  (Creating and maintaining the weekly, monthly and long-term schedule for the Studio)
      li
        | Producing reports, composing correspondence, drafting new contracts and keeping track of invoices, money, salaries, etc.
      li
        | Creating management-level reports as well as presentations if needed.
      li
        | Provide direct administrative support as needed, including scheduling appointments, meetings, and events, booking travel, maintaining a filing system, mailing and shipping packages, and updating contact database and employee list.
      li
        | Oversee and maintain office equipment for uninterrupted function, identify and fulfill office supply needs, maintain and manage vendors, and coordinate food delivery as needed
      li
        | Manage all aspects of the office’s space/infrastructure planning (moves, adds, and changes to workstations) and provide answers, resources, and solutions as requested

